The paper discusses the use of machine learning tools for automatic sensor profiling in wireless sensor networks and the Internet of Things. Specifically, it focuses on lossy compression scenarios where the application tolerates some distortion of the gathered signal in return for improved energy efficiency. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as network infrastructure (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM).
